8
00:00:26,860 --> 00:00:28,778
Have a happy Christmas, everyone.

9
00:00:29,696 --> 00:00:30,613
Hello!

10
00:00:38,204 --> 00:00:39,956
There really isn't much time left.

11
00:00:41,291 --> 00:00:42,208
Are you scared?

12
00:00:44,461 --> 00:00:45,295
No.

13
00:00:46,421 --> 00:00:48,173
Kind of looking forward to it.

14
00:00:49,215 --> 00:00:50,133
The asteroid?

15
00:00:50,633 --> 00:00:54,262
Yeah. It'll go, "Ta-da,"
and show up in the night sky.

16
00:00:55,055 --> 00:00:56,389
I don't want to miss that.

17
00:01:03,021 --> 00:01:04,022
Where's Ha-yul?

18
00:01:04,105 --> 00:01:06,983
Oh, I think she's asleep.

19
00:01:18,328 --> 00:01:20,330
Are you going to stay together to the end?

20
00:01:20,830 --> 00:01:23,750
Of course. The three of us
will be together no matter what.

21
00:01:24,250 --> 00:01:27,378
Yes, and when the asteroid comes,
Min-ho will be with us too.

22
00:01:28,588 --> 00:01:30,256
-Hae-chan.
-Yeah?

23
00:01:30,340 --> 00:01:32,550
What will I get for Christmas this year?

24
00:01:34,427 --> 00:01:36,679
Santa Claus is still around, right?

25
00:01:38,807 --> 00:01:40,391
Stuff like that doesn't exist now.

26
00:01:46,272 --> 00:01:47,357
No, that's not true.

27
00:01:47,440 --> 00:01:49,651
Santa Claus may not be around,
but Mrs. Claus is.

28
00:01:49,734 --> 00:01:53,238
She's going to bring you a gift, okay?

29
00:02:13,299 --> 00:02:15,176
Why are you standing there like that?

30
00:02:17,804 --> 00:02:20,557
Aren't you cold? It's cold out here.

31
00:02:21,474 --> 00:02:24,978
I was just thinking about
how we're having a good time by ourselves.

32
00:02:36,406 --> 00:02:37,240
Mi-ryeong.

33
00:02:46,207 --> 00:02:47,292
Let's say goodbye to Min-ho.

